      <hedline>
        <hl1>Let's Try Again on Health Care</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David E Peterson letter cautions that even the most elaborate health insurance system cannot provide health care for everyone without more doctors (Sept 24 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Toward Universal Coverage'' (editorial, Sept. 24):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Toward Universal Coverage'' (editorial, Sept. 24):</p>
        <p>What you do not recognize is that even the most elaborate health insurance system cannot provide health care for everyone if the average doctor already works long hours to provide health care for 83 percent of the people. We need more doctors. It's as simple as that.</p>
        <p>DAVID E. PETERSON  Winter Park, Fla., Sept. 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
